IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: PROVIDE AID TO TAMPA BAY CHARITIES.
IRS990.MissionDesc: PROVIDE AID TO TAMPA BAY AREA CHARITIES THROUGH FUNDRAISING EVENTS CENTERED AROUND PROFESSIONAL GOLF.
IRS990.Desc: THE 2023 VALSPAR CHAMPIONSHIP, TAMPA BAY'S PGA TOUR EVENT, GENERATED CHARITABLE CONTRIBUTIONS OF $1,189,548 FOR CHARITY. THE TOURNAMENT'S CHARITABLE INITIATIVES COME THROUGH THE SPONSORING ORGANIZATION, COPPERHEAD CHARITIES INC.COPPERHEAD CHARITIES, NOW HAS NOW GENERATED ROUGHLY $50 MILLION FOR CHARITY SINCE 1977 THROUGH THE SPONSORSHIP OF PROFESSIONAL GOLF TOURNAMENTS IN THE TAMPA BAY AREA.(SEE CONTINUATION AT SCHEDULE O.)THE TOTAL INCLUDES MONEY RAISED THROUGH TICKET SALES AND OTHER TOURNAMENT PROCEEDS. APPROXIMATELY 70 AREA CHARITIES ARE BENEFITING FROM THE 2023 TOURNAMENT. COPPERHEAD CHARITIES MADE MANY DIRECTED DONATIONS IN 2023 WITH TAMPA GENERAL HOSPITAL, HABITAT FOR HUMANITY OF PINELLAS AND WEST PASCO COUNTIES, ST. PETERSBURG COLLEGE FOUNDATION, AND AREA CHAPTERS OF THE FIRST TEE AMONG THE KEY CHARITIES BENEFITING.AN INDEPENDENT ECONOMIC IMPACT STUDY PERFORMED BY THE UNIVERSITY OF SOUTH FLORIDA COLLEGE OF BUSINESS SPORT AND ENTERTAINMENT MANAGEMENT PROGRAM AND SPORTSECONOMICS, LLC FOUND THAT TOURNAMENT ACTIVITIES TRANSLATE TO AN ANNUAL ECONOMIC IMPACT OF OVER $64 MILLION TO THE TAMPA BAY AREA.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE TOURNAMENT HAS THE "BIRDIES FOR TAMPA BAY CHARITIES" PROGRAM, WHICH HAS LOCAL CHARITIES SOLICIT PLEDGES THAT ARE WRITTEN TO THE VALSPAR CHAMPIONSHIP. AT THE END OF THE PROGRAM, THOSE PLEDGES AND ADDITIONAL FUNDS FROM THE TOURNAMENT ARE GRANTED TO THE RESPECTIVE CHARITIES. THE TOURNAMENT ONLY ALLOWS DOCUMENTED 501(C)(3) NON PROFIT CHARITIES TO PARTICIPATE IN THIS PROGRAM.

THE ORGANIZATION ENTERED INTO A RABBI TRUST AGREEMENT IN AUGUST 2018 WITH AN INDIVIDUAL FROM MANAGEMENT IN ORDER TO RETAIN THE EMPLOYEE THROUGH THE 2022 VALSPAR CHAMPIONSHIP. THE AGREEMENT ACTS SIMILAR TO A DEFERRED COMPENSATION PLAN AND REQUIRED AN INITIAL DEPOSIT OF $100,000. THE INITIAL DEPOSIT WAS DEPOSITED INTO THE TRUST ACCOUNT ON AUGUST 8, 2018. THE AGREEMENT ALSO REQUIRES ADDITIONAL ANNUAL PAYMENTS NOT TO EXCEED $100,000 EACH SUBSEQUENT YEAR FOR THE 2019 THROUGH 2022 VALSPAR CHAMPIONSHIP. ANNUAL PAYMENT AMOUNTS ARE AT THE DISCRETION OF THE ORGANIZATION'S BOARD OF DIRECTORS. IN JULY 2023, THE ORGANIZATION ENTERED INTO AN EXECUTIVE SUPPLEMENT RETIREMENT AGREEMENT WITH ITS TOURNAMENT DIRECTOR, WHEREBY THE ORGANIZATION AGREES TO (A) PAY $100,000 FOR THE 2023 VALSPAR CHAMPIONSHIP AND (B) PAY AN AMOUNT NOT TO EXCEED $100,000 EACH SUBSEQUENT YEAR FROM 2024 THROUGH 2025 IN WHICH THE TOURNAMENT DIRECTOR PERFORMS SERVICES IN ITS ROLE FOR EACH RESPECTIVE TOURNAMENT YEAR, SUBJECT TO CERTAIN CONDITIONS.

COPPERHEAD CHARITIES, INC. CONTRACTS WITH A SPORTS MANAGEMENT ORGANIZATION FOR THE ADMINISTATION OF ITS EMPLOYEES. UNDER THIS AGREEMENT, ALL EMPLOYEES OF COPPERHEAD ARE IN ACTUALITY EMPLOYEES OF THE SPORTS MANAGEMENT ORGANIZATION. DUE TO THIS AGREEMENT, COPPERHEAD CHARITIES DOES NOT FILE A FORM W-3 TRANSMITTAL OF WAGE AND TAX STATEMENTS, BUT RATHER THE SPORTS MANAGEMENT ORGANIZATION WILL FILE FORM W-3 THAT WOULD INCLUDE THE EMPLOYEES OF COPPERHEAD CHARITIES. AS OF MAY 31, 2023, COPPERHEAD CHARITIES WAS UTILIZING 13 EMPLOYEES THROUGH THE SPORTS MANAGEMENT ORGANIZATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 3
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION HAS ENTERED INTO A SPORTS EVENT MANAGEMENT AND MARKETING AGREEMENT (THE "AGREEMENT") WITH PRO LINKS SPORTS OF TAMPA, LLC. PRO LINKS IS A FULL-SERVICES GOLF MANAGEMENT COMPANY THAT PROVIDES MANAGEMENT AND MARKETING FUNCTIONS FOR THE VALSPAR CHAMPIONSHIP EFFECTIVE JUNE 1, 2014. PRO LINKS, THROUGH ITS AFFILIATES, MANAGES AND MARKETS VARIOUS PGA TOUR-SANCTIONED GOLF TOURNAMENTS SIMILAR TO THE VALSPAR CHAMPIONSHIP THROUGHOUT THE COUNTRY. THE AGREEMENT PROVIDES THAT PRO LINKS WILL MANAGE ALL ASPECTS OF THE VALSPAR CHAMPIONSHIP, INCLUDING SALES AND MARKETING, COURSE OPERATIONS, TOURNAMENT OPERATIONS, AND ACTIVITIES INVOLVING PLAYERS, HOSPITALITY AND VOLUNTEERS. TO FULFILL ITS RESPONSIBILITIES UNDER THE AGREEMENT, PRO LINKS WILL ASSIGN VARIOUS EMPLOYEES AND CONTRACTORS TO THE PERFORMANCE OF SERVICES WITHIN THE AGREEMENT. THE AGREEMENT SHALL REMAIN IN EFFECT FROM ITS INITIAL TERM AND SHALL RUN CO-TERMINUS WITH THE TITLE SPONSOR AGREEMENT, INCLUDING ANY RENEWALS OR EXTENSIONS. THE ORGANIZATION COMPENSATES PRO LINKS FOR ALL EMPLOYMENT AND TOURNAMENT EXPENSES AS OUTLINED IN THE AGREEMENT. IN ADDITION, THE ORGANIZATION PAYS AN ANNUAL MANAGEMENT FEE, TOTALING $531,307 FOR THE FISCAL YEAR ENDED MAY 31, 2023, PLUS AN ANNUAL PERFORMANCE BONUS BASED ON NET TOURNAMENT PROCEEDS (AS DEFINED IN THE AGREEMENT). THE ORGANIZATION PAID PRO LINKS APPROXIMATELY $2,340,000 FOR THE YEAR ENDED MAY 31, 2023. THIS AMOUNT INCLUDES EMPLOYMENT AND TOURNAMENT EXPENSES, ANNUAL MANAGEMENT FEE, AND ANNUAL PERFORMANCE BONUS.

ALL OFFICERS, DIRECTORS AND KEY EMPLOYEES HAVE BEEN MADE AWARE OF THE POLICY AND ARE EXPECTED TO DISCLOSE ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS AND TO RECUSE THEMSELVES FROM ANY DISCUSSION OR VOTE RELATED TO THAT MATTER.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE COMPENSATION OF THE PRESIDENT OF THE ORGANIZATION IS DETERMINED THROUGH A PROCESS BY WHICH INFORMATION IS GATHERED REGARDING SALARIES PAID TO INDIVIDUALS IN SIMILAR POSITIONS AT OTHER ORGANIZATIONS. THIS INFORMATION IS USED TO HELP THE BOARD ARRIVE AT THE PRESIDENT'S COMPENSATION PACKAGE, WHICH IS SPELLED OUT IN A FORMAL EMPLOYMENT CONTRACT. THE ORGANIZATION HAS TWO OFFICERS OTHER THAN THE PRESIDENT AND NO OTHER KEY EMPLOYEES. THEIR COMPENSATION IS PROPOSED BY THE PRESIDENT, BASED UPON COMPENSATION PAID FOR SIMILAR POSITIONS IN OTHER ORGANIZATIONS, AND IS APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.
